    <bf:note>
      <bf:Note>
	<rdfs:label>"Covered bonds are debt instruments that have recourse either to the issuing entity or to an affiliated group to which the issuing entity belongs, or both, and upon an issuer default, also have recourse to a pool of collateral (the 'covered pool') separate from the issuer's other assets"--[Section] 1:6.1.</rdfs:label>
      </bf:Note>
    </bf:note>
